{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"fields":{"description":"# WS1 â€” Diff context-assembler + base reviewer\n\n## Why\nThe four-pass code-review gate (parent b744) consumes the shipped review kernel, which needs (a) a `context` string the Pass-2 verifier re-grounds against â€” for code review that is the DIFF, not plan text â€” and (b) a Pass-1 base reviewer that always runs and emits the bounded overlay-escalation signal. This story builds those two foundations everything else wires onto.\n\n## What\n- A diff context-assembler that turns a `(base, head)` range / unified diff + changed-files list into the kernel `context` string (parallel to plan-review's `assemble_context(...).plan_text`).\n- The base code-reviewer finder prompt (front-matter contract) that emits Pass-1 evidence findings AND `recommend_overlays: [{overlay_id, reason}]`, with `overlay_id` constrained to the FIXED overlay-catalog enum (the model cannot invent an overlay; a concrete one-line reason is required).\n- The `recommend_overlays` output contract (a registered output schema) so the workflow can read it as a named step output.\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/assemble.py` â€” the diff context assembler (reuses the existing diff read in `code_review.py`).\n- `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/code-review-base.md` â€” base reviewer prompt (front-matter `inputs`/`outputs`/`execution_mode`/`dimension`).\n- The `recommend_overlays` output schema (in `src/rebar/schemas/` + the prompt `outputs:` binding).\n- OUT OF SCOPE: the overlay catalog itself (WS2), the union/dispatch (WS3).\n\n## Specifics pinned (plan-review remediation 2026-06)\n- **Overlay-id ENUM ownership (resolves the WS2 cross-dependency):** WS1 OWNS the closed overlay-id enum as a small shared constant (`OVERLAY_IDS` in `code_review/registry.py` or a constants module); WS2 authors the catalog CONTENT (prompts + `applies_to` globs) keyed by that enum. So AC3's enum validation has its dependency satisfied WITHIN WS1 â€” WS2 only adds content, not the enum.\n- **\"CI drift gate\" = the existing derived-prompt-index drift check.** Observable in-session: `rebar workflow validate` passes; `python -c \"from rebar.llm.prompts import get_prompt; get_prompt('code-review-base')\"` resolves; regenerating the derived prompt index yields no diff.\n- **Stakeholder:** the rebar maintainers operating the Gerrit code-gate (and downstream contributors whose changes the gate reviews).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A diff context-assembler produces the kernel `context` string from a `(base, head)` range or a unified-diff input + changed-files list; unit-tested on a sample diff.\n- [ ] The base reviewer prompt is a contract-bearing front-matter prompt that resolves via the prompt library and passes the CI drift gate.\n- [ ] The base reviewer's output carries `recommend_overlays`, each `overlay_id` validated against the fixed catalog enum; out-of-enum ids are dropped (not errored), with a test asserting the drop.\n- [ ] The base reviewer runs as a STANDALONE agent step (not a batch criterion), so `recommend_overlays` survives (the batch runner aggregates only `findings`).\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1782621536780804001,"uuid":"ee207411-5559-4992-825b-dbcfa725b568"}